---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Services | Ali Uyar" canonicalPath="/services" description="Ways Ali Uyar helps teams with AI systems, technical product decisions, and reliable delivery.">
  <SiteHeader />
  <main id="main" class="page-wrap max-w-5xl py-14 md:py-18">
    <section class="page-intro">
      <h1 class="title-balance text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-5xl">What I do</h1>
      <p class="page-lede">
        I help teams get clear on the real problem, whether it is already visible or only starting to show up.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="subtle-card p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">System Review</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
          System Review is for teams that need clarity on architecture, reliability, and what to fix first.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">Typical outcomes</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
          <li>A clearer picture of the main technical risks.</li>
          <li>A practical list of what matters now and what can wait.</li>
          <li>A sharper direction for the next steps.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="subtle-card p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Implementation</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
          Implementation is for teams that know the direction and need the work to become more disciplined and reliable.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">Typical outcomes</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
          <li>AI workflows that are more stable and easier to evaluate.</li>
          <li>Checks and measurement built into the work.</li>
          <li>A handover the team can actually use.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="subtle-card p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Advisory</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
          Advisory is for teams that want sharper product, architecture, or sequencing decisions before committing further.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">Typical outcomes</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
          <li>Clearer decisions before time and money are spent in the wrong place.</li>
          <li>Less confusion about where AI helps and where it does not.</li>
          <li>Technical product input that works for both builders and decision-makers.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-14 border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))/0.72] pt-8 md:grid md:grid-cols-5 md:gap-8">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">How I work</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-7 text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
          I prefer small engagements with a clear question or bottleneck.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 md:col-span-2 md:mt-0">
        <ol class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-[rgb(var(--fg))]">1. Understand the problem.</span>
            We get clear on the real issue, not just the symptoms around it.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-[rgb(var(--fg))]">2. Keep the scope tight.</span>
            We decide what is worth doing now and what can wait.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-[rgb(var(--fg))]">3. Leave something useful behind.</span>
            The result should still help the team after the engagement ends.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10 border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))/0.72] pt-5">
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[rgb(var(--muted))]">
        If this seems relevant, the easiest way to start is an email on the
        <a href="/contact" class="focus-ring ml-1 transition-colors hover:text-[rgb(var(--fg))] hover:underline">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <SiteFooter />
</BaseLayout>
